## 6. Tool Rendering (renderCall / renderResult)

```typescript
pi.registerTool({
  name: "my_tool",
  // ...
  renderCall(args, theme, context) {
    // args: the tool call arguments
    // theme: current theme for styling
    // context: { isStreaming, lastComponent? }
    // Must return Component from @earendil-works/pi-tui
    return new Text(theme.fg("toolTitle", `Tool: ${args.action}`), 0, 0);
  },
  renderResult(result, options, theme, context) {
    // result: { content, details, isError }
    // options: { expanded, isPartial }
    // context: { args, state, lastComponent? }
    // Use context.args instead of copying args into context.state
    // Use context.state only for shared data across call and result slots
    return new Text(result.content[0]?.text ?? "", 0, 0);
  },
  renderShell: "self",  // Optional: complete control over framing
});
```

### Rendering guidelines
```
- Handle isPartial for streaming progress
- Support expanded for detail on demand
- Keep default view compact
- Read context.args in renderResult instead of copying args into context.state
- Use context.state only for data shared across call and result slots
- Reuse context.lastComponent when same component can update in place
- Use renderShell: "self" only when default boxed shell gets in way
```

### Fallback behavior
```
renderCall undefined/throws → Shows tool name
renderResult undefined/throws → Shows raw text from content
```

