Key findings so far. Let me get the full `agent_start` and `agent_end` handlers with complete context.## Answer

**"Working..." does NOT persist after agent finishes.** It is explicitly stopped and removed.

---

## Evidence

### 1. Loader class (`pi-tui/dist/components/loader.js`)

**Constructor** (line 21-29):
```javascript
message = "Loading...";
constructor(ui, spinnerColorFn, messageColorFn, message = "Loading...", indicator) {
    super("", 1, 0);
    this.ui = ui;
    this.spinnerColorFn = spinnerColorFn;
    this.messageColorFn = messageColorFn;
    this.message = message;
    this.setIndicator(indicator);
}
```
- Default message is `"Loading..."` (class field), but pi overrides it via the `message` parameter.
- Constructor calls `setIndicator(indicator)` → calls `this.start()` → calls `restartAnimation()`.

**No `setVisible` method** — Loader has no visibility control. Visibility is managed externally by adding/removing it from a Container.

**`setMessage(msg)`** (line 41-44):
```javascript
setMessage(message) {
    this.message = message;
    this.updateDisplay();
}
```
No guard for null/undefined/empty. Passes raw value to `this.messageColorFn(this.message)` in `updateDisplay()`.

**Spinner always animates** once constructed — `setIndicator` calls `start()`, which calls `restartAnimation()` (line 57-63), which sets a `setInterval` that ticks every `intervalMs` (default 80ms). The interval runs regardless of whether the component is in the UI tree. `updateDisplay()` calls `this.ui.requestRender()` on every tick.

### 2. InteractiveMode (`interactive-mode.js`)

**Default state** (lines 153-157):
```javascript
loadingAnimation = undefined;       // line 153
workingMessage = undefined;         // line 154
workingVisible = true;              // line 155
workingIndicatorOptions = undefined;// line 156
defaultWorkingMessage = "Working...";// line 157
```

**`getWorkingLoaderMessage()`** (line 1352-1353):
```javascript
getWorkingLoaderMessage() {
    return this.workingMessage ?? this.defaultWorkingMessage;
}
```
Falls back to `"Working..."` when `workingMessage` is undefined.

**`createWorkingLoader()`** (line 1355-1356):
```javascript
