    return new Loader(this.ui, 
        (spinner) => theme.fg("accent", spinner),
        (text) => theme.fg("muted", text),
        this.getWorkingLoaderMessage(),  // "Working..." by default
        this.workingIndicatorOptions);
}
```

**`stopWorkingLoader()`** (line 1358-1364):
```javascript
stopWorkingLoader() {
    if (this.loadingAnimation) {
        this.loadingAnimation.stop();
        this.loadingAnimation = undefined;
    }
    this.statusContainer.clear();
}
```

**`setWorkingVisible(visible)`** (line 1365-1377):
```javascript
setWorkingVisible(visible) {
    this.workingVisible = visible;
    if (!visible) {
        this.stopWorkingLoader();
        this.ui.requestRender();
        return;
    }
    if (this.session.isStreaming && !this.loadingAnimation) {
        this.statusContainer.clear();
        this.loadingAnimation = this.createWorkingLoader();
        this.statusContainer.addChild(this.loadingAnimation);
    }
    this.ui.requestRender();
}
```
Only creates loader when `this.session.isStreaming` is true.

**`agent_start` handler** (lines 2222-2247):
```javascript
case "agent_start":
    this.pendingTools.clear();
    if (this.settingsManager.getShowTerminalProgress()) {
        this.ui.terminal.setProgress(true);
    }
    // ... cleanup retry state ...
    this.stopWorkingLoader();           // line 2241: clear any existing loader
    if (this.workingVisible) {          // line 2242: default true
        this.loadingAnimation = this.createWorkingLoader();  // line 2243: creates with "Working..."
        this.statusContainer.addChild(this.loadingAnimation); // line 2244: makes visible
    }
    this.ui.requestRender();
    break;
```

**`agent_end` handler** (lines 2376-2384):
```javascript
case "agent_end":
    if (this.settingsManager.getShowTerminalProgress()) {
        this.ui.terminal.setProgress(false);
    }
    if (this.loadingAnimation) {          // line 2380
        this.loadingAnimation.stop();     // line 2381: stops the interval
        this.loadingAnimation = undefined; // line 2382: drops reference
        this.statusContainer.clear();     // line 2383: removes from UI
    }
    // ...
    this.ui.requestRender();
    break;
```

**Extension API `setWorkingMessage`** (lines 1608-1612):
```javascript
setWorkingMessage: (message) => {
    this.workingMessage = message;
    if (this.loadingAnimation) {
        this.loadingAnimation.setMessage(message ?? this.defaultWorkingMessage);
    }
}
```
Extension API guards null/undefined → falls back to `"Working..."`. But the raw `Loader.setMessage()` does NOT guard.

---

## Definitive Answer

| Phase | Loader state |
|---|---|
| **Before agent_start** | `undefined` — no loader |
| **agent_start** | Loader created with `"Working..."`, added to statusContainer, spinner animating |
| **During streaming** | Loader visible, spinner animating, message updates via `setWorkingMessage` |
| **agent_end** | `loadingAnimation.stop()`, set to `undefined`, `statusContainer.clear()` |
| **After agent_end** | No loader — "Working..." is gone |

**"Working..." does NOT persist.** The `agent_end` handler unconditionally stops the loader, drops the reference, and clears the status container. It only reappears on the next `agent_start`.

## Caveats

- If an extension calls `setWorkingVisible(true)` while `this.session.isStreaming` is false, the loader won't be created — the guard at line 1372 prevents it.
- `Loader.setMessage(null/undefined)` passes the raw value through to the color function — no null guard in the Loader class itself, only in the extension API wrapper.
- The spinner interval keeps ticking even when the Loader is not in the UI tree (e.g., after `stop()` is called, the interval is cleared; but if the Loader object is garbage collected without `stop()`, the interval would leak).## Findings
